news.title: Jaipur development body starts demolition of Laxmi Vilas Hotel
news.para: The project was announced in the Budget speech and Chief Minister Ashok Gehlot is expected to lay the foundation stone on October 2. “The estimated cost of the project is Rs 54 crore and the civic body will invite tenders for the same,” an official said.

news.title: Rajasthan housing ministry briefs CM about drive on resolving land issues
news.para: For the first time in the state, the local bodies will issue yellow colour lease deeds for residential, red for commercial, blue for institutional and purple for industrial establishments.

news.title: Over 24,000 defaulters owe Rs 82.81 crore to Chandigarh Housing Board
news.para: The list includes small flats given under slum rehabilitation schemes; affordable rental housing scheme units, which were also given to slum dwellers; commercial units and residential flats in different sectors and colonies.
